&gt;interested to know how it would have contributed to increasing
&gt;the car's performance...
">

The floor was tested to not bend at 500Nm pressure.
If you have a solid fitted floor, it may flex slightly, but will not
move much more if the pressure is higher at racing speeds, because the
bolts will not allow it to flex any more.
However, if you have it fitted onto springs, the springs will allow
some movement as they compress and then some more as the floor
flexes(just as the bolted ones do) when the springs bottom out.
A couple of mms of anything in F1 could mean a much better aero
efficiency and of course performance..

